      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So it's essentially a competitive inhibition at the active site. Can you explain the structural reason why the binding is non-selective? Like, why doesn't the ibuprofen molecule prefer the COX-2 binding pocket over COX-1? I'm trying to visualize the spatial/structural aspect of the binding.",
